    <h2 id="features">1. Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Engine-agnostic search</strong> via <code>Magento\CatalogSearch\Model\ResourceModel\Fulltext\Collection</code> — works on Elasticsearch 7, Elasticsearch 8, OpenSearch, and MySQL with one code path.</li>
        <li><strong>Three live result sections</strong> — Products (with image, name, SKU, price), Categories (with item count), CMS Pages.</li>
        <li><strong>Popular searches</strong> — quick-pick chips driven by the live <code>search_query</code> popularity counter that Magento maintains for every storefront search.</li>
        <li><strong>Recent searches</strong> — last 6 stored in <code>localStorage</code>, cleared on cache flush.</li>
        <li><strong>Highlighted matches</strong> — every result highlights the substring the user typed.</li>
        <li><strong>Keyboard navigation</strong> — arrow keys, Enter, Escape — full accessibility.</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile-first</strong> — bottom-anchored fixed dropdown on phones, big touch targets, 16px input font (no iOS zoom).</li>
        <li><strong>Theme-token aware</strong> — colors come from <code>theme-config.json</code> via CSS custom properties so the look matches the rest of the Hyva theme.</li>
        <li><strong>Dedicated cache type</strong> — <code>panth_search_autocomplete</code> in cache management. Auto-invalidated when products / categories / CMS pages change.</li>
        <li><strong>Bot &amp; abuse prevention</strong> — see §4.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="architecture">2. Architecture &amp; engine compatibility</h2>
    <p>Single AJAX endpoint at <code>/searchautocomplete/ajax/suggest?q=&lt;term&gt;&amp;form_key=&lt;key&gt;</code>. Pipeline:</p>
    <pre>RequestValidator → RateLimiter → Cache lookup
                                       │
                              ┌────────┴────────┐
                              │ ProductProvider │ ← Fulltext\Collection (ES/OS/MySQL)
                              │ CategoryProvider│ ← catalog_category_entity
                              │ CmsPageProvider │ ← cms_page (storefront-scoped)
                              │ PopularProvider │ ← search_query
                              └────────┬────────┘
                                       │
                                Cache write → JSON response</pre>
    <p>The product path uses <code>\Magento\CatalogSearch\Model\ResourceModel\Fulltext\Collection</code>, which delegates to whichever <em>search engine adapter</em> Magento is configured to use:</p>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Engine</th><th>Magento setting</th><th>Status</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Elasticsearch 7</td><td><code>catalog/search/engine = elasticsearch7</code></td><td><span class="pill pill-on">Supported</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Elasticsearch 8</td><td><code>catalog/search/engine = elasticsearch8</code></td><td><span class="pill pill-on">Supported</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>OpenSearch</td><td><code>catalog/search/engine = opensearch</code></td><td><span class="pill pill-on">Supported</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td>MySQL fallback</td><td><code>catalog/search/engine = mysql</code></td><td><span class="pill pill-on">Supported</span></td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>No engine-specific HTTP client, no DSL templates. The merchant changes engines from the admin and the autocomplete instantly follows.</p>

    <h3>Filters applied to product results</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Status</strong> — only enabled products (<code>status = 1</code>)</li>
        <li><strong>Visibility</strong> — only "Catalog, Search" + "Search" (<code>visibility IN (3, 4)</code>) — same as <code>/catalogsearch/result</code></li>
        <li><strong>Store scope</strong> — current store id only</li>
        <li><strong>Stock</strong> — when <code>cataloginventory/options/show_out_of_stock = 0</code>, OOS products are hidden via <code>StockHelper::addInStockFilterToCollection</code></li>
        <li><strong>Permission scope</strong> — customer group is part of the cache key so guest vs logged-in users never share results</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Filters applied to category results</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Active</strong> — only <code>is_active = 1</code></li>
        <li><strong>Store root</strong> — restricted by <code>path LIKE '1/&lt;rootCategoryId&gt;/%'</code> so multi-store installs never leak categories from a sibling store</li>
        <li><strong>Root excluded</strong> — the store root itself is never returned</li>
        <li><strong>URL resolves</strong> — categories without a built URL are dropped post-filter</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Filters applied to CMS page results</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Active</strong> — only <code>is_active = 1</code></li>
        <li><strong>Store scope</strong> — <code>addStoreFilter()</code> joins <code>cms_page_store</code>; both the current store id and 0 (= "All Stores") are honoured exactly like the storefront</li>
        <li><strong>Identifier required</strong> — pages without an identifier are dropped (cannot build a URL)</li>
        <li><strong>System pages excluded</strong> — <code>no-route</code>, <code>enable-cookies</code>, <code>home</code>, <code>privacy-policy-cookie-restriction-mode</code></li>
        <li><strong>Composite text search</strong> — title OR meta_keywords OR meta_description OR content_heading OR identifier</li>
    </ul>

