    <h2 id="security">4. Security model — what blocks attackers</h2>
    <p>The endpoint sits in front of the catalog search index, the CMS table, and the category tree, so it is an attractive target for scraping, brute-force enumeration, and credential / cart spam. Eight independent layers run on every request:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Method whitelist</strong> — only GET / POST. Anything else is a 200 with empty payload (does not leak the endpoint shape).</li>
        <li><strong>POST body size cap</strong> — POST bodies larger than 4 KB are dropped before any work happens.</li>
        <li><strong>User-Agent gate</strong> — empty + 22 known bot patterns (curl, wget, python-requests, go-http-client, okhttp, java/, scrapy, phantomjs, headlesschrome, puppeteer, playwright, sqlmap, nikto, masscan, etc.).</li>
        <li><strong>X-Requested-With</strong> — must equal <code>XMLHttpRequest</code>. Blocks direct browser nav and most curl probes.</li>
        <li><strong>Same-origin</strong> — Origin / Referer host must equal the store base-URL host. Blocks cross-site enumeration and CSRF replay.</li>
        <li><strong>Honeypot</strong> — hidden <code>website</code> field must be empty. Bots fill every field; real humans never see it.</li>
        <li><strong>Form key</strong> — Magento's session-bound, rotating CSRF token must validate.</li>
        <li><strong>Query sanitisation + length bounds</strong> — control bytes stripped, quotes removed, length must be 2-64 chars.</li>
        <li><strong>Per-IP sliding-window rate limit</strong> — 60 req/min/IP+UA+store. Cache hits don't count, so legitimate users are never throttled.</li>
    </ol>
    <p><strong>Output side:</strong> JSON-encoded responses are XSS-safe; the JS clients escape every field before HTML insertion (only the highlight substitution generates <code>&lt;mark&gt;</code> tags). Response headers set:</p>
    <pre>Cache-Control: private, no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow, nosnippet
Referrer-Policy: same-origin</pre>
    <div class="ok"><strong>Defence in depth.</strong> Eight layers means an attacker has to bypass eight independent checks to reach the search engine. Cached responses are isolated per (store, customer group, query) so a compromise of one cache row never leaks another customer's view.</div>
    <div class="warn"><strong>Layer 9 (recommended):</strong> put a WAF in front (Cloudflare / Fastly / AWS WAF) and rate-limit POSTs to <code>/searchautocomplete/*</code> to e.g. 120 req/min/IP at the edge.</div>

    <h2 id="performance">5. Performance &amp; caching</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Hot path:</strong> warm queries return in &lt;5 ms because the cache lookup short-circuits all four providers.</li>
        <li><strong>Cold path:</strong> 30-80 ms typical on a 100 k-SKU catalog (ES/OpenSearch ~20 ms, category DB ~5 ms, CMS DB ~5 ms, popular DB ~5 ms, JSON encode ~5 ms).</li>
        <li><strong>Cache key:</strong> <code>sha1(storeId | groupId | mb_strtolower(query))</code> — guests and logged-in customers never see each other's cached results.</li>
        <li><strong>Cache tags:</strong> rows are tagged with <code>cat_p</code>, <code>cat_c</code>, <code>cms_p</code>, and the dedicated <code>PANTH_SEARCH_AUTOCOMPLETE</code> tag, so a product save / category save / CMS page save automatically clears the relevant rows on the next reindex / cache flush.</li>
        <li><strong>Manual flush:</strong> <code>bin/magento cache:clean panth_search_autocomplete</code></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="themes">6. Hyva &amp; Luma integration</h2>
    <p>The module ships <strong>two templates</strong> sharing one ViewModel:</p>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Theme</th><th>Template</th><th>Stack</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Hyva</td><td><code>view/frontend/templates/hyva/searchbox.phtml</code></td><td>Tailwind utilities + Alpine.js component, no external CSS/JS files</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Luma</td><td><code>view/frontend/templates/searchbox.phtml</code></td><td>Vanilla JS bundle + standalone CSS file under <code>web/js</code> + <code>web/css</code></td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>Both templates render an identical UX: the same dropdown layout, the same color palette (sourced from <code>app/design/frontend/Panth/Infotech/web/tailwind/theme-config.json</code> via CSS custom properties), the same keyboard shortcuts, the same recent / popular / categories / pages sections, and the same "see all results" CTA. Layout swap is handled by the <code>hyva_default</code> handle.</p>

    <h2 id="extending">7. Extending — adding new content types</h2>
    <p>To surface a new entity (e.g. blog posts, FAQs, testimonials) in the dropdown:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Create <code>Model/Suggestion/MyProvider.php</code> implementing <code>search(string $query): array</code>.</li>
        <li>Inject it into <code>Controller/Ajax/Suggest.php</code> (constructor + execute()).</li>
        <li>Add a <code>section_heading</code> + render block to both templates.</li>
        <li>Add a config toggle / limit field to <code>etc/adminhtml/system.xml</code>.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="troubleshooting">8. Troubleshooting</h2>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Cause</th><th>Fix</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Dropdown never opens</td><td>Module disabled, or layout container not present in the theme</td><td>Verify <code>panth_searchautocomplete/general/enabled = 1</code>; check the layout XML container name matches your theme.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>0 product results despite typing real SKUs</td><td>Search index empty or stale</td><td><code>bin/magento indexer:reindex catalogsearch_fulltext</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td>"rejected: true" in JSON response</td><td>Form key expired, bot UA, missing X-Requested-With, or cross-origin</td><td>Open browser dev tools, inspect the request headers; reload the page to refresh form_key.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>"throttled: true" in JSON response (HTTP 429)</td><td>Rate limit hit</td><td>Wait 60 seconds, or raise the limit under Configuration → Bot &amp; Abuse Prevention.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Stale results after editing a product</td><td>Cache type not flushed</td><td><code>bin/magento cache:clean panth_search_autocomplete</code> (or wait for the TTL).</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Categories from another store appearing</td><td>Path filter mis-set (should never happen)</td><td>Open a bug — the provider already restricts by <code>path LIKE '1/&lt;rootCategoryId&gt;/%'</code>.</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>CLI reference</h2>
    <pre>
# Manually flush the autocomplete cache
bin/magento cache:clean panth_search_autocomplete

# Enable / disable the cache type
bin/magento cache:enable  panth_search_autocomplete
bin/magento cache:disable panth_search_autocomplete

# Reindex the catalog search index (the engine the providers query)
bin/magento indexer:reindex catalogsearch_fulltext

# Verify the engine in use
bin/magento config:show catalog/search/engine
</pre>
